obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (21654)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The Proviso omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21654&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Contempt of Courts Act, 1971.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (21655)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21655&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "contempt of court" means civil contempt or criminal contempt;`
  line
  line `(b) "civil contempt" means wilful disobedience to any judgment, decree, direction, order, writ or`
  line `other process of a court or wilful breach of an undertaking given to a court;`
  line
  line `(c) "criminal contempt" means the publication (whether by words, spoken or written, or by signs,`
  line `or by visible representations, or otherwise) of any matter or the doing of any other act whatsoever`
  line which—
  line
  line `(i) scandalises or tends to scandalise, or lowers or tends to lower the authority of, any`
  line `court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) prejudices, or interferes or tends to interfere with, the due course of any judicial`
  line `proceeding; or`
  line
  line `(iii) interferes or tends to interfere with, or obstructs or tends to obstruct, the administration of`
  line `justice in any other manner;`
  line
  line `(d) "High Court" means the High Court for a State or a Union territory, and includes the court of`
  line `the Judicial Commissioner in any Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (21656)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Innocent publication and distribution of matter not contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21656&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be guilty`
  line `of contempt of court on the ground that he has published (whether by words, spoken or written, or by`
  line `signs, or by visible representations, or otherwise) any matter which interferes or tends to interfere with, or`
  line `obstructs or tends to obstruct, the course of justice in connection with any civil or criminal proceeding`
  line `pending at that time of publication, if at that time he had no reasonable grounds for believing that the`
  line `proceeding was pending.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act or any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, the publication of any such matter as is mentioned in sub-section (1) in connection with any civil`
  line `or criminal proceeding which is not pending at the time of publication shall not be deemed to constitute`
  line `contempt of court.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be guilty of contempt of court on the ground that he has distributed a`
  line `publication containing any such matter as is mentioned in sub-section (1), if at the time of distribution he`
  line `had no reasonable grounds for believing that it contained or was likely to contain any such matter as`
  line `aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply in respect of the distribution of—`
  line
  line `(i) any publication which is a book or paper printed or published otherwise than in conformity`
  line `with the rules contained in section 3 of the Press and Registration of Books Act, 1867 (25 of 1867);`
  line
  line `(ii) any publication which is a newspaper published otherwise than in conformity with the rules`
  line `contained in section 5 of the said Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, a judicial proceeding—`
  line
  line `(a) is said to be pending—`
  line
  line `(A) in the case of a civil proceeding, when it is instituted by the filing of a plaint or otherwise,`
  line
  line `(B) in the case of a criminal proceeding under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), or any other law—`
  line
  line `(i) where it relates to the commission of an offence, when the charge-sheet or challan is`
  line `filed, or when the court issues summons or warrant, as the case may be, against the accused,`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, when the court takes cognizance of the matter to which the`
  line `proceeding relates, and`
  line
  line `in the case of a civil or criminal proceeding, shall be deemed to continue to be pending until it is`
  line `heard and finally decided, that is to say, in a case where an appeal or revision is competent, until the`
  line `appeal or revision is heard and finally decided or, where no appeal or revision is preferred, until the`
  line `period of limitation prescribed for such appeal or revision has expired;`
  line
  line `(b) which has been heard and finally decided shall not be deemed to be pending merely by reason`
  line `of the fact that proceedings for the execution of the decree, order or sentence passed therein are`
  line pending.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (21657)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Fair and accurate report of judicial proceeding not contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21657&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions`
  line `contained in section 7, a person shall not be guilty of contempt of court for publishing a fair and accurate`
  line `report of a judicial proceeding or any stage thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (21658)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Fair criticism of judicial act not contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21658&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be guilty of contempt of court`
  line `for publishing any fair comment on the merits of any case which has been heard and finally decided.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (21659)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Complaint against presiding officers of subordinate courts when not contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21659&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A person`
  line `shall not be guilty of contempt of court in respect of any statement made by him in good faith concerning`
  line `the presiding officer of any subordinate court to—`
  line
  line `(a) any other subordinate court, or`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court,`
  line
  line `to which it is subordinate.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "subordinate court" means any court subordinate to a High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (21660)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Publication of information relating to proceedings in chambers or in camera not contempt except in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21660&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, a person shall not be guilty`
  line `of contempt of court for publishing a fair and accurate report of a judicial proceeding before any court`
  line `sitting in chambers or in camera except in the following cases, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) where the publication is contrary to the provisions of any enactment for the time being in`
  line force;
  line
  line `(b) where the court, on grounds of public policy or in exercise of any power vested in it, expressly`
  line `prohibits the publication of all information relating to the proceeding or of information of the`
  line `description which is published;`
  line
  line `(c) where the court sits in chambers or in camera for reasons connected with public order or the`
  line `security of the State, the publication of information relating to those proceedings;`
  line
  line `(d) where the information relates to a secret process, discovery or invention which is an issue in`
  line proceedings.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), a person shall not be guilty of`
  line `contempt of court for publishing the text or a fair and accurate summary of the whole, or any part, of an`
  line `order made by a court sitting in chambers or in camera, unless the court has expressly prohibited the publication thereof on grounds of public policy, or for reasons connected with public order or the security`
  line `of the State, or on the ground that it contains information relating to a secret process, discovery or`
  line `invention, or in exercise of any power vested in it.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (21661)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Other defences not affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21661&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall be construed as implying that`
  line `any other defence which would have been a valid defence in any proceedings for contempt of court has`
  line `ceased to be available merely by reason of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21662)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Act not to imply enlargement of scope of contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21662&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall be`
  line `construed as implying that any disobedience, breach, publication or other act is punishable as contempt of`
  line `court which would not be so punishable apart from this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21663)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of High Court to punish contempts of subordinate courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21663&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every High Court shall`
  line `have and exercise the same jurisdiction, powers and authority, in accordance with the same procedure and`
  line `practice, in respect of contempts of courts subordinate to it as it has and exercises in respect of contempts`
  line `of itself:`
  line
  line `Provided that no High Court shall take cognizance of a contempt alleged to have been committed in`
  line `respect of a court subordinate to it where such contempt is an offence punishable under the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21664)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of High Court to try offences committed or offenders found outside jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21664&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line A
  line `High Court shall have jurisdiction to inquire into or try a contempt of itself or of any court subordinate to`
  line `it, whether the contempt is alleged to have been committed within or outside the local limits of its`
  line `jurisdiction, and whether the person alleged to be guilty of contempt is within or outside such limits.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21665)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Punishment for contempt of court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21665&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act or in`
  line `any other law, a contempt of court may be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that the accused may be discharged or the punishment awarded may be remitted on apology`
  line `being made to the satisfaction of the Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—An apology shall not be rejected merely on the ground that it is qualified or`
  line `conditional if the accused makes it bona fide.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, no court shall impose a`
  line `sentence in excess of that specified in sub-section (1) for any contempt either in respect of itself or of a`
  line `court subordinate to it.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where a person is found guilty of a civil`
  line `contempt, the court, if it considers that a fine will not meet the ends of justice and that a sentence of`
  line `imprisonment is necessary shall, instead of sentencing him to simple imprisonment, direct that he be`
  line `detained in a civil prison for such period not exceeding six months as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the person found guilty of contempt of court in respect of any undertaking given to a court`
  line `is a company, every person who, at the time the contempt was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of business of the company, as well as the company, shall be`
  line `deemed to be guilty of the contempt and the punishment may be enforced, with the leave of the court, by`
  line `the detention in civil prison of each such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to such`
  line `punishment if he proves that the contempt was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent its commission.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), where the contempt of court referred to`
  line `therein has been committed by a company and it is proved that the contempt has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of the contempt and the punishment may be enforced, with the leave of the court, by the`
  line `detention in civil prison of such director, manager, secretary or other officer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of sub-sections (4) and (5),—`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21666)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Contempts not punishable in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 2006, s. 2, for section 13 (w.e.f. 17-3-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21666&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Contempts not punishable in certain cases.—Notwithstanding anything contained in any law`
  line `for the time being in force,—`
  line
  line `(a) no court shall impose a sentence under this Act for a contempt of court unless it is satisfied`
  line `that the contempt is of such a nature that it substantially interferes, or tends substantially to interfere`
  line `with the due course of justice;`
  line
  line `(b) the court may permit, in any proceeding for contempt of court, justification by truth as a valid`
  line `defence if it is satisfied that it is in public interest and the request for invoking the said defence is`
  line `bona fide.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (21667)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Procedure where contempt is in the face of the Supreme Court or a High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21667&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) When`
  line `it is alleged, or appears to the Supreme Court or the High Court upon its own view, that a person has been`
  line `guilty of contempt committed in its presence or hearing, the Court may cause such person to be detained`
  line `in custody, and, at any time before the rising of the Court, on the same day, or as early as possible`
  line `thereafter, shall—`
  line
  line `(a) cause him to be informed in writing of the contempt with which he is charged;`
  line
  line `(b) afford him an opportunity to make his defence to the charge;`
  line
  line `(c) after taking such evidence as may be necessary or as may be offered by such person and after`
  line `hearing him, proceed, either forthwith or after adjournment, to determine the matter of the charge;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) make such order for the punishment or discharge of such person as may be just.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where a person charged with contempt`
  line `under that sub-section applies, whether orally or in writing, to have the charge against him tried by some`
  line `judge other than the Judge or Judges in whose presence or hearing the offence is alleged to have been`
  line `committed, and the Court is of opinion that it is practicable to do so and that in the interests of proper`
  line `administration of justice the application should be allowed, it shall cause the matter to be placed,`
  line `together with a statement of the facts of the case, before the Chief Justice for such directions as he may`
  line `think fit to issue as respects the trial thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, in any trial of a person charged with`
  line `contempt under sub-section (1) which is held, in pursuance of a direction given under sub-section (2), by`
  line `a Judge other than the Judge or Judges in whose presence or hearing the offence is alleged to have been`
  line `committed, it shall not be necessary for the Judge or Judges in whose presence or hearing the offence is`
  line `alleged to have been committed to appear as a witness and the statement placed before the Chief Justice`
  line `under sub-section (2) shall be treated as evidence in the case.`
  line
  line `(4) Pending the determination of the charge, the Court may direct that a person charged with`
  line `contempt under this section shall be detained in such custody as it may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall be released on bail, if a bond for such sum of money as the Court thinks`
  line `sufficient is executed with or without sureties conditioned that the person charged shall attend at the time`
  line `and place mentioned in the bond and shall continue to so attend until otherwise directed by the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Court may, if it thinks fit, instead of taking bail from such person, discharge`
  line `him on his executing a bond without sureties for his attendance as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (21668)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Cognizance of criminal contempt in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-3-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21668&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of a criminal contempt, other`
  line `than a contempt referred to in section 14, the Supreme Court or the High Court may take action on its`
  line `own motion or on a motion made by—`
  line
  line `(a) the Advocate-General, or`
  line
  line `(b) any other person, with the consent in writing of the Advocate-General, ^1`
  line [or]
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(c) in relation to the High Court for the Union territory of Delhi, such Law Officer as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, or any other`
  line `person, with the consent in writing of such Law Officer.]`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any criminal contempt of a subordinate court, the High Court may take action on a`
  line `reference made to it by the subordinate court or on a motion made by the Advocate-General or, in relation`
  line `to a Union territory, by such Law Officer as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Every motion or reference made under this section shall specify the contempt of which the person`
  line `charged is alleged to be guilty.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "Advocate-General" means,—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the Supreme Court, the Attorney-General or the Solicitor-General;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the High Court, the Advocate-General of the State or any of the States for which`
  line `the High Court has been established;`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to the court of a Judicial Commissioner, such Law Officer as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (21669)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Contempt by judge, magistrate or other person acting judicially.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21669&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of any law for the time being in force, a judge, magistrate or other person acting judicially`
  line `shall also be liable for contempt of his own court or of any other court in the same manner as any other`
  line `individual is liable and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to any observations or remarks made by a judge, magistrate or`
  line `other person acting judicially, regarding a subordinate court in an appeal or revision pending before such`
  line `judge, magistrate or other person against the order or judgment of the subordinate court.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (21670)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Procedure after cognizance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21670&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notice of every proceeding under section l5 shall be served`
  line `personally on the person charged, unless the Court for reasons to be recorded directs otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) The notice shall be accompanied,—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of proceedings commenced on a motion, by a copy of the motion as also copies of`
  line `the affidavits, if any, on which such motion is founded; and`
  line
  line `(b) in case of proceedings commenced on a reference by a subordinate court, by a copy of the`
  line reference.
  line
  line `(3) The Court may, if it is satisfied that a person charged under section 15 is likely to abscond or keep`
  line `out of the way to avoid service of the notice, order the attachment of his property of such value or amount`
  line `as it may deem reasonable.`
  line
  line `(4) Every attachment under sub-section (3) shall be effected in the manner provided in the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the attachment of property in execution of a decree for payment of`
  line `money, and if, after such attachment, the person charged appears and shows to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Court that he did not abscond or keep out of the way to avoid service of the notice, the Court shall order`
  line `the release of his property from attachment upon such terms as to costs or otherwise as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person charged with contempt under section 15 may file an affidavit in support of his`
  line `defence, and the Court may determine the matter of the charge either on the affidavits filed or after taking`
  line `such further evidence as may be necessary, and pass such order as the justice of the case requires.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (21671)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Hearing of cases of criminal contempt to be by Benches.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21671&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every case of criminal contempt`
  line `under section 15 shall be heard and determined by a Bench of not less than two judges.`
  line
  line `(2) Sub-section (1) shall not apply to the Court of a Judicial Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (21672)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21672&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall lie as of right from any order or decision of the High Court in the`
  line `exercise of its jurisdiction to punish for contempt—`
  line
  line `(a) where the order or decision is that of a single judge, to a Bench of not less than two judges of`
  line `the Court;`
  line
  line `(b) where the order or decision is that of a Bench, to the Supreme Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the order or decision is that of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner in any`
  line `Union territory, such appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Pending any appeal, the appellate Court may order that—`
  line
  line `(a) the execution of the punishment or order appealed against be suspended;`
  line
  line `(b) if the appellant is in confinement, he be released on bail; and`
  line
  line `(c) the appeal be heard notwithstanding that the appellant has not purged his contempt.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person aggrieved by any order against which an appeal may be filed satisfies the High`
  line `Court that he intends to prefer an appeal, the High Court may also exercise all or any of the powers`
  line `conferred by sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an appeal to a Bench of the High Court, within thirty days;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an appeal to the Supreme Court, within sixty days,`
  line
  line `from the date of the order appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (21673)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Limitation for actions for contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21673&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No court shall initiate any proceedings of contempt,`
  line `either on its own motion or otherwise, after the expiry of a period of one year from the date on which the`
  line `contempt is alleged to have been committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (21674)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Act not to apply to Nyaya Panchayats or other village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21674&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act`
  line `shall apply in relation to contempt of Nyaya Panchayats or other village courts, by whatever name`
  line `known, for the administration of justice, established under any law.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (21675)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Act to be in addition to, and not in derogation of, other laws relating to contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21675&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law`
  line `relating to contempt of courts.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (21676)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Supreme Court and High Courts to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21676&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Supreme Court or, as the case`
  line `may be, any High Court, may make rules, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, providing for`
  line `any matter relating to its procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (21677)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Repeal.
  content `The Contempt of Courts Act, 1952 (32 of 1952), is hereby repealed.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029&sectionId=21677&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00005_197170_1517807319029
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
